## Color

### Chip component

Use `palette.[semantictheme].light` for outlined surfaces (text + border) — except `warning`, which uses `palette.warning.main`.

Reason: `warning` resolves to a yellow-ish, gold hue, typically. The `light` shade of warning lacks contrast on light backgrounds. `main` is the smallest step that keeps contrast acceptable for outlined treatment. Do not "normalize" warning to `light` for consistency. It's a perceptual constraint, not a token-naming bug.

Mapping:

| color   | outlined tone                       |
|---------|-------------------------------------|
| default | `text.primary`                      |
| success | `success.light`                     |
| info    | `info.light`                        |
| warning | `warning.main` (yellow exception)   |
| error   | `error.light`                       |
